    $( Ratio test for convergence of a complex infinite series.  If the ratio
       ` A ` of the absolute values of of successive terms in an infinite
       sequence ` F ` is less than 1 for all terms beyond some index ` B ` ,
       then the infinite sum of the terms of ` F ` converges to a complex
       number.  Equivalent to first part of Exercise 4 of [Gleason] p. 182. $)
    cvgrati $p |- ( ( ( A e. RR /\ A < 1 ) /\ ( B e. NN /\ A. x e. NN (
  B <_ x -> ( abs ` ( F ` ( x + 1 ) ) ) < ( A x. ( abs ` ( F ` x ) ) ) ) ) ) ->
                 E. y ( + seq1 F ) ~~> y ) $=
      ( vz vw cv cn wcel cexp co wceq wa copab eqid cvgratlem5 ) ABGHCDEGIZJKHI
      CSLMNOGHPZFTQR $.
